.TH JARVIS 1 "March 2026" "0.3.0" "Jarvis User Manual"
.SH NAME
jarvis \- Local-First AI Orchestrator with Strict Security and ERS
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B jarvis
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fICOMMAND\fR]
.br
.B jarvis
'\fINATURAL LANGUAGE PROMPT\fR'
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B jarvis
is a heavy-duty local-first AI orchestrator designed for NixOS. It implements a principled, **Capability-Based Access Control (CBAC)** security model (Trust Levels 0-4) and an **External Reasoning System (ERS)** for multi-step tasks. Since V3, **Shadow Mode** is disabled; every sensitive action (filesystem, network, subprocess) is strictly gated and requires explicit user approval unless auto-granted.
.SH KEY ARCHITECTURAL COMPONENTS
.TP
.B Security Manager
The core gatekeeper. Enforces trust ceilings and handles interactive/OOB approvals. Tracks session identification via tokens stored in the Vault.
.TP
.B ERS (External Reasoning System)
Executes complex workloads via YAML-defined chains. Each step runs in an isolated child security context with auto-revocation of temporary grants.
.TP
.B Model Hub
A unified router for local (Ollama) and cloud models. Standardized 600s timeouts ensure stability for CPU-bound inference.
.TP
.B Antigravity IDE Layer
Custom LSP bridge for Neovim providing asynchronous code actions (Explain, Fix, Refactor) with session-level isolation.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Displays the health of all Jarvis background services (systemd), Ollama load status, current budget, and session authentication status.
.TP
.B start / stop
Starts or stops all background services (Ingest, Health, Coding Agent).
.TP
.B pause / resume
Suspends or continues AI inference by sending SIGSTOP/SIGCONT to the Ollama process.
.TP
.B uptime
Shows how long each background service has been running.
.TP
.B pending
Lists all active out-of-band (OOB) capability requests from IDE or remote sessions.
.TP
.B approve \fIID\fR
Grants a pending capability request. Use \fBdeny \fIID\fR to reject.
.TP
.B cap [list|grant|revoke] [\fICAP\fR]
Granular capability management. \fBgrant\fR adds a persistent permission; \fBrevoke\fR removes it.
.TP
.B associate [\fICATEGORY\fR | list | remove \fICATEGORY\fR]
Links the current directory to a knowledge category for context-aware RAG.
.TP
.B config [set|get|list|reset] [\fIKEY\fR] [\fIVAL\fR]
Manage user preferences (e.g., \fCmodels.default_local\fR). \fBreset\fR restores factory defaults.
.TP
.B set-key \fIPROVIDER\fR \fIKEY\fR
Securely stores an encrypted API key in the Vault. Supported: \fCanthropic\fR, \fCopenai\fR, \fCgoogle\fR, \fCdeepseek\fR, \fCgroq\fR, \fCopenrouter\fR.
.TP
.B keys
List and verify the status of all configured API keys.
.TP
.B index [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
Indexes the current codebase for the coding agent. Supports \fB--category\fR and \fB--privacy\fR [0-3] flags.
.TP
.B ingest \fIURL/FILE\fR
Indexes documents into the RAG knowledge base. 
.TP
.B learn \fI[TOPIC | URL]\fR
Assisted language learning or direct ingestion with metadata.
.TP
.B query "\fIQUESTION\fR"
Performs a RAG search against the Vault databases. Automatically uses associations from the current directory.
.TP
.B dashboard
Launches the Rust TUI monitor.
.TP
.B backup / archive
Creates backups or compressed archives of the Jarvis codebase and Vault.
.SH ERS INTENTS
When provided with natural language, Jarvis routes to specific ERS chains:
.TP
.I 'research ...'
Triggers \fCresearch_deep.yaml\fR for extensive web and local analysis.
.TP
.I 'summarize git ...'
Triggers \fCgit_summarize.yaml\fR to generate human-readable changelogs.
.TP
.I 'validate nixos ...'
Triggers \fCnixos_verify.yaml\fR to check configuration sanity using local models.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.IP "\fBJARVIS_ROOT\fR"
Override the default project directory.
.IP "\fBVAULT_ROOT\fR"
Override the secure data storage root (Default: /THE_VAULT/jarvis).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /THE_VAULT/jarvis/databases/security_audit.db
Central audit trail and pending grant storage.
.TP
.I /THE_VAULT/jarvis/databases/knowledge.db
RAG knowledge base and embeddings.
.TP
.I /THE_VAULT/jarvis/context/active_session_token
The source of truth for session authentication.
.SH SECURITY PROTOCOL
Capabilities (e.g., \fCfile_read\fR, \fCshell_exec\fR) are requested dynamically. If not auto-granted by a trust level:
.IP 1.
The process raises \fCCapabilityPending\fR.
.IP 2.
The user is notified via CLI (Interactive) or long-polling (OOB).
.IP 3.
The task pauses until \fBjarvis approve\fR is executed.
